div.p:
Certain cases where there have been exchanges of correspondence in connection with the resumption of diplomatic relations are as follows: Mexico, 1923;
Ibid., 1923, vol. ii, p. 522. Nicaragua, 1926;See
ibid., 1926, vol. ii, footnote 35, p. 807. and Brazil, 1827.See American State Papers, Foreign Relations, vol. vi, pp. 1021–1121. While these notes have referred to the resumption of diplomatic relations, they have also dealt with the settlement of certain questions which were at issue between the two Governments.
